io.smudgr.api

Interface ApiCommand

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ReflectableType
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AppPort, CanvasPort, ControlPause, ControlPlay, ControlRecord, ControlSaveFrame, FileList, FileWorkingDirectory, ParameterSet, PerformanceFPS, ProjectGet, ProjectNew, ProjectOpen, ProjectSave, RackGet, RackSmudgeAdd, RackSmudgeMove, RackSmudgeRemove, SmudgeComponentAdd, SmudgeComponentMove, SmudgeComponentRemove, SmudgeGet, SourceCurrentSet, SourceLibraryGet, SourceThumbnail, TypesSmudge, TypesSmudgeComponent

    public interface ApiCommand
extends ReflectableType
    Interface for defining the behavior of a unique command.

    execute(ApiMessage) is called when the API is invoked with a packet referencing he string returned by getCommand()

    Every class that implements ApiCommand is instantiated only once at runtime using the default constructor.

    See Also:
    ApiInvoker, ApiMessage

      • getTypeCategoryIdentifier

        default java.lang.String getTypeCategoryIdentifier()
        Description copied from interface: ReflectableType
        This should return a unique identifier of the category of this type.

        The name that this type category is identified to the user with may differ from this identifier. This concept is similar to a 'slug'.

        Implementations of a type should not override this method.

        The String returned by this method should not be changed between versions.

        Specified by:
        getTypeCategoryIdentifier in interface ReflectableType
        Returns:
        String that will enumerate this type category across versions of the application
